<h2> The "perplexity" of Nordio</h2>
"I do not know the acts and as a guaranteeer I always think of the presumption of innocence. It seems to me that it is a matter of facts that date back to a few years ago and that the investigation was not born today but time back," says Nordio. "I exercised 40 years as a prosecutor and rarely asked for precautionary measures after years of investigation. My perplexity is never the moment when the precaution is taken against the impending election," he explains, but "if I have technical perplexities, it concerns a measure of the time when the crime was committed and the investigation began." Even if he asks whether it is "justice to watchmaking", the minister answers: "I do not like phrases made or common to hear, I prefer to keep in mind the principle of presumption of innocence."
&nbsp;
"I am a guarantee, for me a person is guilty only when he is sentenced to third degree of judgment," comments the national secretary of Forza Italia Antonio Tajani>, who in a note proclaims "the extraneity" of FI and announces the suspension of members Maurizio and Arturo Testa, involved in the investigation and the domiciles because accused of electoral corruption, aggravated by the purpose of facilitating Cosa Nostra".
&nbsp;
As for Fratelli d'Italia>, the line is expressed by the group leader in the Chamber Tommaso Foti, which at the end of the day assures "maximum attention to the facts of the Liguria Region, like the one lent for the facts of Bari and in general of Puglia", which involved the centerleft. "We hope that the investigations will be rapid and that there will be full clarity on the facts, which are the subject of the measures of the judicial authority today, and we trust that everyone will act in maximum transparency," Foti points out. While the League line is scanned by the deputy minister at Mit, Ligurian Edward Rix>i, who merely expresses "support and firm solidarity" at Toti.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
From October president of Noi moderates, after the experiences of Cambiamo and Courage Italy, Toti led from 2015 a junta of center-right, supported by his civic list (Cambiamo con Toti Presidente), Forza Italia, Lega e FdI. In view of the policies of 2022 he had formed an electoral cartel along with Noi with Italy by Maurizio Lupi, and the Udc by Lorenzo Cesa. But, in the face of the risk that the centrists did not exceed the barrier threshold, FdI took charge of eleven centrist candidates (We with Italy and Courage Italy), in the close agreement between the leaders of the centre-right before the vote. In view of the Europeans, We moderates of Lupi instead opted for a unitary list with FI (Udc with the League) and Toti invited its supporters to vote generically for all parties of the district.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Salvin: "The survey lasted four years and closed it now"</h2>
"I don't care to comment on the timing of the investigation; "if he is as quiet as he says, if he thinks he is a good governor, which I am convinced of, he will prove it. And so from my point of view, it must not be resigned," said Vice-Premier Matteo Salvini> in Milan, on the margin of the opening conference of the Transpotec Logitec Fair and NME Next Mobility Exibition 'The transport of goods and people between present and future', commenting the investigation. To whom he asked if the timing was suspected a month by the Europeans, Salvini, smiling, added: "I don't comment on the timing. Surely, if an investigation lasted four years they had their reasons to close it now. But don't comment."
&nbsp;
<h2>Towards the European vote
FdI, FI and Lega are engaged in the final rush of the election campaign >: Meloni will gather - in Rome, probably in Piazza del Popolo - the candidates of FdI on June 1st, Forza Italia and Noi moderate will do the same on May 13th (in the presence of the president of the commission Ue von Der Leyen) and also the League is studying the various initiatives on the territory (on May 13th, for example, there will be Matteo Salvini> and General Roberto Vannacci >a Bari). But in Transatlantic today it is populated as a macigno the news of the investigation of Genoa.
&nbsp;
Parliamentary work will be suspended at the House on 3 June, although in fact already on 28 May there will be the 'fuggi fuggì, in the coalition of government we will discuss reforms but will go 'long and then the main topic becomes the relationship between politics and judiciary' and above all the arrest, to the domiciles, of the president of the Liguria Region.
<h2> Toti's resignation? FdI does not exclude anything
FI is cautious while Brothers of Italy seems at first to go further. "Let's see the cards", the premise of a weight exponent, "but in the meantime we indicate to Toti a way out". To speak publicly is the Ligurian coordinator of FdI, Matteo Rosso: the resignation of Toti? "Nothing can be excluded," he said at first, and then said: "FdI expresses the utmost solidarity with President Giovanni Toti and, trusting in the work of the judiciary, renews trust to the governor." The party's position is still waiting. "It's Toti who decides what to do. But that's not even a month," explains a parliamentary source. No pressure on the governor, "is not a matter of timing", the concern is linked to the possibility that the investigation is widened and that the majority in Region may not be operational. "And for us - says the same source - would be chaos, because at the moment we don't even have an alternative candidate."
&nbsp;
In any case, the centre will wait for developments in the investigation. "We are guaranteed. It doesn't seem to me that the charges against Toti stand," says a FI-weighted exponent. "Who knows why these investigations always arrive before a vote," he ironifies a member of the League. Meanwhile, the order of precautionary custody of the maxi inquiry for corruption in Genoa was sent by the chief prosecutor, Nicola Piacente, to the parliamentary commission Antimafia. The district is still standing next to the governor.
<h2> The resiko of applications
The argument of the majority is that the Ligurian governor will demonstrate his innocence but the hypothesis of a step backwards of Toti, not excluded from FdI, could 'reopen' the resiko of candidatures in the coalition. The next regions that will go to the vote are Umbria (where they voted in October 2019), and, to follow, Campania, Marche, Puglia, Tuscany and Veneto (it was voted in September 2020). In Liguria, it would have had to vote in this last election round, then in September 2025, and Toti could not have relapsed for the ban of third mandate in force for the presidents of Region, having been elected for the second time in 2020 (with 56.13% of preferences against 38.90% went to the candidate of the center leftist Ferruccio Sansa). In accordance with Article 41 of the Regional Statute, the Vice-President of the Ligurian junta, the Legislator Alessio Piana>, replaces the independent governor.
&nbsp;
It is now necessary to understand how the investigation will evolve and above all how long the precautionary measure will last towards Toti. In the event that Toti resigned in the coming weeks, we could go to the autumn vote in shortcoming with Umbria and, possibly, with Emilia-Romagna (the likely election of Stefano Bonaccini in Strasbourg could lead to the early vote). At this point, the candidate's theme would be in the centre.
&nbsp;
In Transatlantic in the morning there were already possible 'variable geometry'. Who, between leghisti and FI, hypothesized a Rixi race at the Palace of navigation. Those who gave for certain the candidacy of Rosso, Ligurian coordinator of Brothers of Italy, a party that has long sought to lead a Northern Region. The first hypothesis - that is the possibility for the League to lead the Liguria - would then compensate the party of Matteo Salvini of the possible 'loss' &nbsp; of the Venetian fief, where Luca Zaia can not relapse in 2025, obliged to a stop after the second term. Although - he observes a source of FdI - "the League at this moment is weak in Liguria". However, neither Rixi nor Rosso would be available to the state for an application that the investigation would make uphill.
&nbsp;
But it is also necessary to see if the other road will be accessible, that is, that of prolonged regency of Piana, until the expiration of the legislature, also considering the fact that the name of the latter has appeared recently (but it is not investigated) in an investigation of the Procura of Genoa on vip festini with drugs and escort, stamped as "fake news" from the interested party.
<h2> The Pd-M5s-Avs axis calls for a step back</h2>
On the front of the oppositions, from the axis Pd-M5s-Avs comes the strong demand for resignation of President Toti. "The combination of politics and private enterprises with milionary interests linked to public administration is a real disease to be eradicated. And it is the main reason why I believe that Toti must resign and that the word should be returned to the citizens of Liguria", says Nicola Fratoianni>, secretary of Italian Left. "It is necessary to go quickly to new elections. Only new elections can bring political clarity to a region that is now a concentrate of interests, that is, companies, companies and people who have financed the election campaign of President Toti, and who are then the same companies that have obtained permissions or delibere from the same Region", says Angelo Bonelli> of Green and Left Allenza. "Elections immediately" is also the line of the Democratic Party.
&nbsp;
The leaders of Liguria, in a note, break the Hindus and ask that immediately begin that process of regeneration of the regional institutions of which the former Minister Andrea Orlando speaks. "It must close the season of the center of Liguria. Toti dimetta and there are immediately new elections", we read in the text signed by the leaders Pd of Genoa and Liguria. A request that goes beyond the judicial record. It moves, rather, from negative judgment on the regional government: "In these years the Democratic Party at all levels has denounced the damage and consequences that this policy management has caused to health, work, infrastructure, social services." This, along with the "just distance from the electoral deadlines, calls for civic mobilization: in the name of the morality of politics and a different idea of Liguria". A position that follows Orlando's. The exponent dem is among the first to urge, in the face of a "desolant square", a process of regeneration that cannot begin if not with the resignation of the governor: "It must be avoided that this very serious short circuit prejudges the interests of the region and the big investments that concern it. It is therefore necessary to prevent the situation from falling. There is a need to start a strong process of regeneration in the interest of the region and Ligurians."
&nbsp;
Toti's resignation is also Giuseppe Conte>: "The investigation has just come out, precise and serious facts are emerging. It is good that" the president of Liguria "takes the consequences", explains Conte in the margin of the General States of the accountants. An appointment, that of Rome, to which also the Minister of Justice, Carlo Nordio.
&nbsp;
Count and Nordio do not cross in the audience, but their looks the most classic of the barrel and answer. The Guardasigilli expresses perplexity on the domicile precautionary case arranged for Toti: "The danger of escape, of pollution of evidence and the reiteration of the crime is the reasons for which it can be stopped", but "after so many years from the event that occurred and the investigation" is difficult that "they can still exist". On the contrary, Conte believes that which has shown itself in Genoa "a very great wound to democracy" that raises "a national moral question" and "it is certainly not putting the mordacchia to the toghe that can be found a solution". A reference even so implied to the reform which bears the name of the minister and which is expected "in short" in the Council of Ministers. On Nordio there is also the Head of Justice of the Pd, Debora Serracchiani: "The words of Nordio seem to be those of the defense of President Toti, not of course those who should act with fair institutional collaboration."
The precaution of centrists
Matteo Renzi does not participate in the choir calling for Toti's resignation.> Remembering that "we are at the opposition of Toti", the leader of Italy alive emphasizes that "more reason we are guaranteed. We will vote for the judgments. I never thought that a judicial measure should automatically affect the country's political life." Speculation position at Action: "It is too long the list of inquired governors, banged in the newspapers with clamors and then prosciolti or acquitted, from Pittella to Fontana, from Oliverio to De Luca, from Zingaretti to Bonaccini to name a few, not to take with the feet of lead the accusations against Giovanni Toti", says MP Enrico Costa.&nbsp;

