"For the international missions to be extended - it is remembered in the text of the majority - the total annual maximum consistency of the quotas of the Armed Forces used in the operating theatres is pairs to 11.166 units, while the financial requirement for the planned duration is pairs altogether to euros 1.365.148.673,00, of which European 1.075.798.673,00 for bonds payable in 2024 and European 289.350.000,000,000.000,00 per bonds es es es".
<br It should also be recalled that "for the implementation of the new missions > concerning the deliberation of 26 February 2024" the total annual maximum total consistency of the quotas of the Armed Forces used "is 834 units, while the total financial requirement required is 45,863,901 and, therefore, the maximum consistency of the national quotas used in the missions for the year 2024 reaches the 12,000 units". And it is noted that "as long as the extension of the ongoing missions, to the expense of the Ministry of Defense must be added 30 million to the Presidency of the Council of Ministers for the maintenance of the information-operative device of the Aise, 3.864.387 euros to the charge of the Ministry of the Interior, for the missions of the Police Forces", 83.897 euros to the charge of the Ministry of Justice and 18.816.279 euros to the Ministry of Finance
&nbsp;
And therefore "the total total expenditure on missions in 2024, given by the total sum of the prorogations and the new missions, "is therefore 1 billion 825 million 440 thousand and 680 euros, > little greater than the total financial requirement for the extension of the missions in 2023, which amounted to Euro 1.779.510.236".
&nbsp;
"The international crises in progress, from the conflict in Ukraine > to what is happening in the Middle East and the Red Sea, > have seriously jeopardized the hold of the international order, determining direct effects on the security of Italy and Europe, in a global context that continues to be characterized by factors of fluidity &nbsp; and instability", emphasizes in the draft resolution of the majority.
&nbsp;
"Italy, which is the seat of the Presidency of the G7>, still maintains - as a firm point of its action both its membership in the European Union and the Atlantic Alliance, as well as multilateralism on the United Nations system; the action of our country is aimed, in all crisis theatres, to the protection of international peace and security in a framework of open and inclusive global collaboration, with a priority strategic attention to the region of the Mediterranean 'allargated' and to the Western Balkans, whose balances are deeply touched by the crisis in Eastern Europe'. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>AVS, stop rearmo</h2>
"The debate on the missions of Italy takes place in a dramatic international context, for some pre-war, to put global security at risk. In the world 2,200 billion dollars were spent last year, 9% more than the previous year, resources destined to increase, since the race to the rearmament seems the only way, to remain to the statements of the governments. For us, instead, peace and effort for peace is more than ever indispensable: from the recognition of the State of Palestine, to a lasting peace conference in the Middle East, to a political action against the war of looting in Ukraine where we do not want to send troops but we ask for the European commitment to peace. In this context, we are concerned with the government's plan to weaken political-parliamentary control over missions: That is why we are presenting our alternative resolution." So in Hall Luana Zanella, group leader of Green Alliance and Left at the House.
&nbsp;
<h2>M5S, our soldiers are likely to be on the front line
"The mad and blind bellicist strategy is consistently going towards its inevitable and dramatic epilogue: the sending of NATO troops, which would risk involving our troops deployed along the new iron curtain running from the Baltic to the Black Sea where we today have the most powerful Italian military deployment ever seen in the post-war period. In the face of the concrete risk that our armed forces today deployed in function of deterrence, find themselves in the forefront in a NATO war against Russia, demands from this government a commitment, not in words but with the facts, to stop this escalation before it is too late". The 5 Stars Emma Pavanelli, who spoke in general about military missions abroad, said this in the Chamber.
<br> "Today - resume - Ukraine is still in the position to treat peace: in a few months he's likely to be dealing with a surrender. In addition, the M5s asks the government to guarantee that our participation in the European Ukrainian military training mission never becomes the legal vehicle for direct involvement in the conflict. That is why we demand that in the event that the EU Council proposes to extend the training activities to the Ukrainian territory, the government will come to Parliament in advance to receive from it the political mandate to be made: If in a few months it will be decided at EU level that we must send our soldiers trainers in Ukraine to the front, 'boots on the ground' as they say in jargon, this decision - concludes Pavanelli - must pass to the screening of Parliament. That's the least."
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
